{
    "title": "Phantom Liberty Driving Mission pet",
    "content": "Fuck, finally getting back into Cyberpunk after a year off and picked up Phantom Liberty. I am loving everything about it, they really found a way to integrate the area into the main game in the perfect way. There are 2 generated events I never fail to stop what I am doing when I see them occur. The supply drop and car theft missions. They are relatively fun and challenging and give great rewards. The car thefts are basically a steering wheel icon on the map (they even occur outside of Dog Town I think), you kill one or two enemies that are guarding it, get in and take off to a point on the map miles away. There seems to be a RNG for how each are handled. Just drive (most rare) Drive but the game throws waves of enemies at you to kill you during the trip. 3, Deliver the car in great condition. 4. Deliver the car under a certain time limit. 5. A combo of numbers 2-4. My pet peeve is with #4. Most of the time, the time given to deliver is super unrealistic. A route where if you drove perfectly at full speed, would take you 5 minutes, the game gives you like 3. It doesn't make any sense to me and seems like a bug. The worst part is the fixer calling you and admonishing you for how bad you are. I would love if the game gave you the option to tell the fixer to pound salt with that time limit. Is there a way to cancel out of the mission? The cars seem pretty indestructible. I do find that if you save before getting in the car and reload, the RNG changes."
}

