{
    "title": "I just played The Last Guardian for the first time.",
    "content": "And my god, it's one of the best games I've ever played. Coming from a gamer of decades with several hundred titles played.Sure, a bit wonky camera and platforming, but everything else just comes toghether so perfectly. The simplicity in design and puzzles contradicted in the complexity of the Nest and game world. How little you're allowed to interact with the world vs how much impact your story has. The mysteries presentet in a way that only team ICO can do. And of course the big doofus that accompany you in your journey. Trico is absolutely adorable, and despite a 15 hr first playthrough I almost felt as much for the beast as I do for my own pets. 10/10, will play again, right now."
}

